"title": "8031: trust, importance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8031: trust, importance of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture emphasises the importance of putting one's trust in God. This trust, which is nurtured by an understanding of God's revealed truth, finds expression in a life lived according to his purpose. There are examples in Scripture of proper trust being placed in other people.</p>\n<h2>Grounds for trust in God</h2>\n<h3>Trust in God's power and strength</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:31\">EXO 14:31</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:12\">2TI 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:1-2Sam22:3\">2SA 22:1–22:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2-Ps18:3\">PSA 18:2–18:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:9-Ps9:10\">PSA 9:9–9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:9-Ps115:11\">PSA 115:9–115:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:1-Ps144:2\">PSA 144:1–144:2</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in God's unfailing love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:5\">PSA 13:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:13\">EXO 15:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:7\">PSA 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:7\">PSA 21:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:18\">PSA 33:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps52:8\">PSA 52:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:11\">PSA 147:11</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in God's salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa12:2\">ISA 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:37\">1SA 17:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:4-Ps22:5\">PSA 22:4–22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:2-Ps40:3\">PSA 40:2–40:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa25:9\">ISA 25:9</a></p>\n<h2>Trust nurtured by God's revealed truth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:19-Prov22:21\">PRO 22:19–22:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:30\">PSA 18:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:42\">PSA 119:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:5\">PRO 30:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:36\">JHN 12:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:1-John14:3\">JHN 14:1–14:3</a></p>\n<h2>Expressions of trust in God</h2>\n<h3>Praise and worship</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:5\">PSA 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:7\">PSA 28:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:10\">PSA 64:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:28\">DAN 3:28</a></p>\n<h3>Perseverance in faith</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:4-Isa7:7\">ISA 7:4–7:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:46-Jer51:47\">JER 51:46–51:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:4\">2TH 1:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:35-Heb10:36\">HEB 10:35–10:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2-Heb12:3\">HEB 12:2–12:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:12\">JAS 1:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:11\">JAS 5:11</a></p>\n<h3>Holding on to God's promise</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:56-1Kgs8:57\">1KI 8:56–8:57</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:5\">PSA 130:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:7\">ACT 26:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:20-Rom4:21\">ROM 4:20–4:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:5\">COL 1:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's trust in the Father</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:46\">LUK 23:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:5\">PSA 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:8\">PSA 22:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:43\">MAT 27:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:13\">HEB 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:17\">ISA 8:17</a></p>\n<h2>King Hezekiah's trust in God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:5-2Kgs18:7\">2KI 18:5–18:7</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:20-2Chr31:21\">2CH 31:20–31:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:30\">2KI 18:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa36:15\">ISA 36:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:14-2Kgs19:19\">2KI 19:14–19:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:14-Isa37:20\">ISA 37:14–37:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:20\">2CH 32:20</a></p>\n<h2>Further examples of trust in God</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:12\">RUT 2:12</a> <em>Ruth</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:20\">1CH 5:20</a> <em>the tribes of Reuben, Gad and Manasseh</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:17\">DAN 3:17</a> <em>Shadrach, Meshach and Abednego</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:23\">DAN 6:23</a> <em>Daniel</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:12\">ZEP 3:12</a> <em>the meek and humble</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a> <em>members of the NT churches</em></p>\n<h2>The results of trusting in God</h2>\n<h3>Peace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:3-Isa26:4\">ISA 26:3–26:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:13\">ROM 15:13</a></p>\n<h3>Security</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:3\">PSA 37:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:10\">PSA 32:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:1\">PSA 125:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:25\">PRO 29:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:16\">ISA 28:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:13\">ISA 57:13</a></p>\n<h3>Protection from danger</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:1-Ps25:3\">PSA 25:1–25:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:14-Ps31:15\">PSA 31:14–31:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:7\">PSA 32:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:18-Ps33:22\">PSA 33:18–33:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:1-Ps91:4\">PSA 91:1–91:4</a></p>\n<h3>Freedom from fear</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:1\">PSA 27:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:4\">PSA 23:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:4\">PSA 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:3-Ps56:4\">PSA 56:3–56:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:10-Ps56:11\">PSA 56:10–56:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:7\">PSA 112:7</a></p>\n<h3>Prosperity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:25\">PRO 28:25</a> <em>In the OT material prosperity is often seen as a sign of the spiritual wealth that belongs to those who trust God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:20\">PRO 16:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:7-Jer17:8\">JER 17:7–17:8</a></p>\n<h3>Strength</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:15\">ISA 30:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:29-Isa40:31\">ISA 40:29–40:31</a></p>\n<h3>Physical life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:20\">PSA 25:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:18\">JER 39:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:11\">JER 49:11</a></p>\n<h2>Trust in people</h2>\n<h3>God's servants entrusted with responsibility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:1-1Cor4:2\">1CO 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:1-Luke16:2\">LUK 16:1–16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:4\">1TH 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a></p>\n<h3>Trust at home and work</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov31:10-Prov31:11\">PRO 31:10–31:11</a> <em>A good wife gives her husband confidence</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:10\">TIT 2:10</a> <em>Employees should be trustworthy.</em></p>\n<h3>Examples of trusting others</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:4\">GEN 39:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:39-Gen41:40\">GEN 41:39–41:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:9\">EXO 19:9</a> <em>Moses to be trusted by Israel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:22\">1CH 9:22</a> <em>the gatekeepers appointed by David and Samuel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:6\">NEH 2:6</a> <em>Nehemiah is trusted by Artaxerxes to return to Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:29-Dan6:2\">DAN 5:29–6:2</a> <em>Daniel given responsibility</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:25\">PHP 2:25</a> <em>Paul's confidence in Epaphroditus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:2</a> <em>Timothy to find others to be entrusted to teach the gospel</em></p>\n<h3>Continued trust in those who fail</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:1-Jonah3:2\">JON 3:1–3:2</a></strong> <em>God re-appoints Jonah despite earlier disobedience.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:15\">JHN 21:15</a> <em>Jesus Christ reinstates Peter after his denial</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:37-Acts15:39\">ACT 15:37–15:39</a> <em>Barnabas gives John Mark a second chance.</em></p>",
